4 December 2014On 5 December 2014 South Africa will commemorate the first anniversary of former President Nelson Mandela s passing. The South African Government encourages the public to: post photos, videos, stories, favourite quotes and pictures of themselves wearing a Mandela t-shirt on social media.The public may also donate books or toys to a child in need and share the former President s passion for helping children. The world is encouraged to observe three (3) minutes of silence on 5 December as to remember Nelson Mandela. The social media campaign for the commemoration of the passing of the former President Mandela is as follows: Hashtag: #RememberMandelaFor more information visit the following webpages:Webpage: http://www.gov.za/commemoration-first-anniversary-nelson-mandela%E2%80%99s-passing Pictures you can use: http://www.mandela.gov.za/gallery/index.htmlFocal social media accountsTwitter accounts: 1. South African Government: https://twitter.com/GovernmentZA 2. The Presidency: https://twitter.com/PresidencyZA 3. Department of Social Development: https://twitter.com/PresidencyZA 4. Department of Communications: https://twitter.com/DoC_Media 5. SA News: https://twitter.com/SAgovnewsFacebook: 1. South African Government: https://www.facebook.com/GovernmentZA 2. Department of Social Development: https://www.facebook.com/pages/Department-of-Social-Development/390232001058697 3. The Presidency: https://www.facebook.com/PresidencyZA 4. SA News: https://www.facebook.com/sanewsgovzaOrder of proceedings for the Public on 05 December 2014For coordination of interviews please contact: Ireen Magwai on 082 440 5676 or ireen@doc.gov.za or Jaconia Kobue on 082 313 4673 or jaconiak@dsd.gov.zaEnquiries: Lumka Oliphant Contact: 083 484 8067Issued by: Department of Social Development